    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "D&C",
        "delineation": "Section",
        "number": 3,
        "summary": "1\u20134, The Lord's course is one eternal round; 5\u201315, Joseph Smith must repent or lose the gift to translate; 16\u201320, The Book of Mormon comes forth to save the seed of Lehi.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The works, and the designs, and the purposes of God cannot be frustrated, neither can they come to naught.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Works of.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jer. 1:8 (7\u20138).",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For God doth not walk in crooked paths, neither doth he turn to the right hand nor to the left, neither doth he vary from that which he hath said, therefore his paths are straight, and his course is one eternal round.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Neh. 9:8; Isa. 45:19; Alma 7:20. TG\u00a0God, Perfection of.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 1:7; 3\u00a0Ne. 18:13 (12\u201314).",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 10:19 (18\u201319); D&C 35:1.",
                        "start": 189,
                        "end": 195
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember, remember that it is not the work of God that is frustrated, but the work of men;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 5:38; Morm. 8:22; D&C 10:38 (38\u201340).",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For although a man may have many revelations, and have power to do many mighty works, yet if he boasts in his own strength, and sets at naught the counsels of God, and follows after the dictates of his own will and carnal desires, he must fall and incur the vengeance of a just God upon him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 19:4.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 6:13 (13\u201314); Mosiah 11:19; D&C 84:73. TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 122
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 9:14; Jacob 4:10; Alma 37:37. TG\u00a0Counsel.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 155
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Carnal Mind; Chastity; Lust.",
                        "start": 215,
                        "end": 221
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Vengeance.",
                        "start": 258,
                        "end": 267
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 1:22.",
                        "start": 273,
                        "end": 277
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, you have been entrusted with these things, but how strict were your commandments; and remember also the promises which were made to you, if you did not transgress them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 37:14.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And behold, how oft you have transgressed the commandments and the laws of God, and have gone on in the persuasions of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 5:21; 20:5; JS\u2014H 1:28 (28\u201329).",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Josh. 23:16 (15\u201316); Alma 12:31. TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Titus 1:14; D&C 45:29; 46:7; JS\u2014H 1:19. TG\u00a0Motivations; Peer Influence.",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 115
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 6
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For, behold, you should not have feared man more than God. Although men set at naught the counsels of God, and despise his words\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Neh. 6:13; Ps. 27:1 (1\u201314); Isa. 57:11; Luke 9:26; John 12:43 (42\u201343); Acts 4:19; D&C 122:9 (4\u20139). TG\u00a0Courage; Fearful.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Num. 15:31 (30\u201331); 2\u00a0Sam. 12:9 (7\u20139); 1\u00a0Ne. 19:7; 2\u00a0Ne. 33:2; Jacob 4:14 (8\u201314). TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yet you should have been faithful; and he would have extended his arm and supported you against all the fiery darts of the adversary; and he would have been with you in every time of trouble.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eph. 6:16; 1\u00a0Ne. 15:24; D&C 27:17.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 115
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 132
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 81:7; Alma 9:17; 38:5.",
                        "start": 183,
                        "end": 190
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold, thou art Joseph, and thou wast chosen to do the work of the Lord, but because of transgression, if thou art not aware thou wilt fall.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 1:25; 1\u00a0Cor. 10:12. TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 140
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But remember, God is merciful; therefore, repent of that which thou hast done which is contrary to the commandment which I gave you, and thou art still chosen, and art again called to the work;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:3.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 173
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Except thou do this, thou shalt be delivered up and become as other men, and have no more gift.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 13:3; D&C 1:33; 121:37 (34\u201337).",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when thou deliveredst up that which God had given thee sight and power to translate, thou deliveredst up that which was sacred into the hands of a wicked man,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 1:29; 5:4 (4, 30\u201331).",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 87
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacred; Sacrilege.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 130
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:6 (6\u20138).",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Who has set at naught the counsels of God, and has broken the most sacred promises which were made before God, and has depended upon his own judgment and boasted in his own wisdom.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 4:10. TG\u00a0Haughtiness; Pride.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this is the reason that thou hast lost thy privileges for a season\u2014",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For thou hast suffered the counsel of thy director to be trampled upon from the beginning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the Lord; see v.\u00a06.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Nevertheless, my work shall go forth, for inasmuch as the knowledge of a Savior has come unto the world, through the testimony of the Jews, even so shall the knowledge of a Savior come unto my people\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 5:39; 1\u00a0Ne. 13:25 (23\u201325); 2\u00a0Ne. 29:4 (4\u20136); D&C 20:26.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 126
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 3:20.",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 167
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Savior.",
                        "start": 173,
                        "end": 179
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And to the Nephites, and the Jacobites, and the Josephites, and the Zoramites, through the testimony of their fathers\u2014",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 13:30; 2\u00a0Ne. 29:12 (12\u201313); Alma 45:14 (10\u201314).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And this testimony shall come to the knowledge of the Lamanites, and the Lemuelites, and the Ishmaelites, who dwindled in unbelief because of the iniquity of their fathers, whom the Lord has suffered to destroy their brethren the Nephites, because of their iniquities and their abominations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Testimony.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Jacob 1:13; Enos 1:13; D&C 10:48 (46\u201352); 109:65.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 26:15; Jacob 3:7. TG\u00a0Doubt.",
                        "start": 110,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Responsibilities toward; Sin.",
                        "start": 146,
                        "end": 154
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 8:2 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 217,
                        "end": 225
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 12:7.",
                        "start": 257,
                        "end": 267
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And for this very purpose are these plates preserved, which contain these records\u2014that the promises of the Lord might be fulfilled, which he made to his people;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 9:3 (3, 5).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Book of Mormon.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Preservation of.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Enos 1:16 (13\u201318); Mosiah 21:4; 3\u00a0Ne. 5:14 (13\u201315); D&C 10:47 (46\u201350).",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 99
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Joseph, People of; Israel, Restoration of.",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And that the Lamanites might come to the knowledge of their fathers, and that they might know the promises of the Lord, and that they may believe the gospel and rely upon the merits of Jesus Christ, and be glorified through faith in his name, and that through their repentance they might be saved. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 30:5 (3\u20136); D&C 28:8 (8\u20139, 14); 32:2; 49:24.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 10:9 (9, 21); Alma 9:24.",
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Morm. 3:21.",
                        "start": 138,
                        "end": 145
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 31:19; Moro. 6:4.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 165
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 7:26 (26, 38).",
                        "start": 206,
                        "end": 215
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}